# arvo-comb — backlog

> **Type-surface reminder**: new entries use `arvo::USize` /
> `Bool` / `UFixed<N, 0, S>` instead of `usize` / `bool` / `u*`;
> `notko::Maybe` / `Outcome` instead of `Option` / `Result`. See
> `rules/type-surface.md`.

## Morton / Hilbert dispatch ordering

Space-filling curve ordering for dispatch interleaving. Same
constraint representation as greedy grouping. Deferred per
polka-dots T3 decisions #71-74 — not day-one.

## Mask256-backed bin_pack variant

`bin_pack` ships with a `Cap` up to 64-ish items per bin (bounded
by internal Mask64 helpers where consumers pair it with
hierarchical co-firing flags). A `Mask256`-backed sibling would
support >64 flags per group. Common pipeline workloads per
polka-dots T5 research stay well under 64 flags, so this is a
non-urgent widening.

## cap_size helper promotion to arvo L0

arvo-comb imports `cap_size` from arvo-bitmask. Same situation as
arvo-graph and arvo-sparse. When the fourth L2 / L3 consumer
surfaces (or when refactor fatigue makes the cross-crate import
annoying), promote the helper into arvo (L0) as a public
`const fn`. Purely additive; removes the cross-crate dependency on
a trivially small helper.
